pageContext.claim: “But if you look at the European Union right now, they're having breakouts like you've never seen before. And, frankly, their numbers are at a level that are much worse than the numbers here.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is comparing apples and oranges by positioning the 27 countries in the European Union plus the U.K., Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein against the U.S. Together those countries recorded 27,233 new cases on Sept. 9, compared with the 26,015 recorded in the U.S.
